allure serve allure-results

allure generate allure-results --clean -o allure-report

allure open allure-report



"allure: command not found": You need to install the Allure command-line tool.
Mac (Homebrew): brew install allureWindows (Scoop): scoop install allure
Manual: Download the binaries from Maven Central, unzip them, and add the bin folder to your system PATH.
Blank Report / Loading Issues: Do not try to open the index.html file directly from your file explorer (e.g., double-clicking it).
Browsers block the necessary AJAX calls for security reasons. You must use allure open or allure serve to view it correctly.

ls / cd navigate to test directory

# Local development (keeps awake)
pytest tests/test_select_options_product.py -v

# CI/CD (doesn't interfere)
pytest tests/test_select_options_product.py --no-sleep-prevention -v


# Run ALL tests
pytest tests/

# Run ONE test file
pytest tests/test_navigation.py

# Run ONE specific test
pytest tests/test_navigation.py::TestCategoryNavigation::test_submenu_item_hover_color_changes

# Run tests matching a name
pytest tests/ -k "navigation"


# Verbose output (show each test)
pytest tests/ -v

# Very verbose (show details)
pytest tests/ -vv

# Show print statements
pytest tests/ -s

# Quiet (only summary)
pytest tests/ -q

# Stop after first failure
pytest tests/ -x

# Stop after 3 failures
pytest tests/ --maxfail=3


# Verbose + show prints + stop on first failure
pytest tests/ -v -s -x

# Everything + short traceback
pytest tests/ -v -s --tb=short

# Just see what passes/fails
pytest tests/ -v --tb=line
